<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/69646269-seenhear"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_100x100-259587f1619f5253426a4fa6fb508831.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/69646269-seenhear">Seenhear</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    I think it's actually fairly clear that Eliot and Bronte went to have an abortion. It could be interpreted that they gave a baby to adoption, but that<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    I think it's actually fairly clear that Eliot and Bronte went to have an abortion. It could be interpreted that they gave a baby to adoption, but that would mean that Bronte hid her pregnancy all the way to full term; not likely, and then he also would have known the sex of the child rather than having to "imagine" that the baby had been a girl, which he claimed to do. If you read their conversation again, it's fairly clear IMO that they aborted a pregnancy for fear of getting caught. I agree with the others that this is partially why Eliot had such an attachment to Emily; he saw himself as her father-figure and she unknowingly, saw him as such also.<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</span>
</div>
</div>
