<div id="review_882437358" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/882437358" />
    <a title="Darth J " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/18974711-darth-j"><img alt="Darth J " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1456429148p2/18974711.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/882437358?book_show_action=true">Mar 15, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Darth J " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Darth J " href="/user/show/18974711-darth-j">Darth J </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/18974711-darth-j?shelf=fast-paced">fast-paced</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/18974711-darth-j?shelf=would-recommend">would-recommend</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer882437358" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7083334189630142245">The best way I could describe it would be <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6101718.The_Magicians__The_Magicians___1_' title='The Magicians (The Magicians, #1) by Lev Grossman' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Magicians</a> meets <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/18302455.The_Circle' title='The Circle by Dave Eggers' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Circle</a>. I was fascinated by the whole concept of understanding how language can affect people and the neurolinguistic elements had me wanting to re-up my lapsed <i>Psychology Today</i> subscription. The twists were about 80% predictable in the story though as you realize that certain characters are actually other ones well before the reveal happens. All the time spent in Australia had me feeling parched, and I don&apos;t know if that&apos;s a good</span>
  <span id="freeText7083334189630142245" style="display:none">The best way I could describe it would be <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6101718.The_Magicians__The_Magicians___1_" title="The Magicians (The Magicians, #1) by Lev Grossman" rel="nofollow noopener">The Magicians</a> meets <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/18302455.The_Circle" title="The Circle by Dave Eggers" rel="nofollow noopener">The Circle</a>. I was fascinated by the whole concept of understanding how language can affect people and the neurolinguistic elements had me wanting to re-up my lapsed <i>Psychology Today</i> subscription. The twists were about 80% predictable in the story though as you realize that certain characters are actually other ones well before the reveal happens. All the time spent in Australia had me feeling parched, and I don't know if that's a good thing or a bad one. Overall, I liked it.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7083334189630142245" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


