<span id="freeTextContainer10087778255624332918">i reread this book to find out if it&apos;s as disappointing as i remember.. yeah it is<br/><br/>this book suffers from the same reason i dislike interstellar.... a very cool concept trampled by ~~~the power of love~~~<br/><br/>but good god the potential this book had 😭<br/><br/>----<br/><br/>It may sound like I hated the book judging by my last status update. I didn&apos;t. I actually <i>loved</i> it but I&apos;m really disappointed by the ending. It&apos;s not really <i> that</i> bad IMO but certainly not my piece of cake.<br/><br/><a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/16158596.Lexicon' title='Lexicon by Max Barry' rel='nofollow noopener'>Lexicon</a> has it all. Great idea, action-packe</span>
  <span id="freeText10087778255624332918" style="display:none">i reread this book to find out if it's as disappointing as i remember.. yeah it is<br /><br />this book suffers from the same reason i dislike interstellar.... a very cool concept trampled by ~~~the power of love~~~<br /><br />but good god the potential this book had 😭<br /><br />----<br /><br />It may sound like I hated the book judging by my last status update. I didn't. I actually <i>loved</i> it but I'm really disappointed by the ending. It's not really <i> that</i> bad IMO but certainly not my piece of cake.<br /><br /><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/16158596.Lexicon" title="Lexicon by Max Barry" rel="nofollow noopener">Lexicon</a> has it all. Great idea, action-packed and fast-paced plot, well-defined distinct characters. It has words, that can erase an entire population of the small town. It has people who persuades another with words only. Art of persuasion! Neurolinguistics! Different people types, where each type has their own words of persuasion! Words which belongs to a fundamental language of human mind! Chase! Murders! Mind control! <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[But in the end everything is WOW! THE POWER OF LOVE! LOVE CAN SAVE US ALL! LOVE LOVE LOVE LOVE LUUUUVVVVV! It is kinda MEH. And unbelievable. And far-fetched. And does it work only for MCs? <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br /><br />Even though I like this book SO much (except the ending), I have few issues it:<br /><br />• What's the goal of that society of poets? What are they doing? Why do they choose "gifted" people and teach them? Why do they experiment on ordinary people? WHY? What's the point of them? There was almost <i>NOTHING</i> about them in the book.<br /><br />• Sometimes the writing was too messy. I couldn't even understand some things. I've even read some chapters in Russian, but it didn't help either. Sometimes it was too confusing and hard to keep up.<br /><br />• <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[I'd rather have Emily succumbed to evil than being controlled by Yeats. That's not that big of an issue, but I expected more from her  <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br /><br />• ENNNDDDINNNNGGGG. <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[I seriously hate that <i>the power of love can conquer it all </i> trope.  <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br /><br />I think that Max Barry didn't unlock the whole potential of the book. The idea is freaking amazing. I still liked it and found it pretty amazing. Until 90% I'd easily give it 5 stars. But DUH.</span>
